Distribution: The new species is only known from few localities in Córdoba Province , Argentina : Pampa de Achala, a highland plateau situated in the Sierras Grandes ( Polop 1989 , 1991 ), three localities in Río Cuarto Department (Cerro de Oro, Puesto Gonzalez and La Ventana, all above 1500 m elevation;
Priotto et al . 1996
), and two additional sites in Pampa de San Luis , Cruz del Eje Department (SW of Pampa de San Luis , 1900 m , and near Cuchilla Nevada , 1700-1800 m ;
Kufner et al . 2004
) ( Fig. 14 ).

Karyotype: 2n = 40. The autosomal pairs 1 to 18 are telocentric and the pair 19 is metacentric. The X chromosomes are subacrocentric and the Y is small metacentric ( Polop 1989 ;
Pinna-Senn et al . 1992
).
